[LoadingHints_UTDeathmatch]
Hint_0=Every weapon has at least two firing modes.  Some have even more that can be used by combining the primary and alternate fire mode in different ways.
Hint_1=To get an extra height boost, press jump again at the peak of a jump.
Hint_2=You can dodge off walls while in the air.
Hint_3=The Shock Combo is a powerful explosion created by shooting a shock core with a shock beam.
Hint_4=There are two ways to use the Rocket Launcher's alt-fire: while loading rockets into the launcher, press the Primary Fire button once to fire them in a tight spiral, or twice to launch them as grenades.
Hint_5=You can toggle the scoreboard display at any time by pressing the Show Scores button.
Hint_6=You can shoot down enemy Redeemer missiles with a well-placed shot.
Hint_7=The UDamage powerup will greatly increase the damage done by all your shots for a limited time.
Hint_8=The Berserk power-up doubles the rate of fire of all your weapons for a limited amount of time.
Hint_9=The Shield Belt will fully absorb up to 100 points of damage.
Hint_10=The Helmet will protect you from 20 points of additional damage, or a single headshot, whichever comes first.
Hint_11=You can use the Impact Hammer's alt-fire EMP to knock a power-up off an enemy player.
Hint_12=The Stinger's alternate fire is slow but lethal, and can be used to pin enemies to walls.
Hint_13=You can feign death to confuse your enemies.
Hint_14=Practice good sportsmanship.  You were a n00b once, too.
Hint_Count=15

[LoadingHints_UTOnslaughtGame]
Hint_0=Using an Orb to capture a Node will also shield it from damage for a short period of time.
Hint_1=Shaped Charges and Redeemer Missiles are the only items that can be used to destroy barricades.
Hint_2=Incoming enemy orbs are visible on the minimap.
Hint_3=If you take any damage while riding the Hoverboard, you will fall to the ground and drop the Orb if you were carrying it.
Hint_4=The Paladin has a large shield, and can discharge the shield to create a very effective area of effect attack against close range targets.
Hint_5=You can use the Hoverboard's Grapple to tow behind passing friendly vehicles.
Hint_6=You can heal a friendly vehicle with the Link Gun alt-fire.
Hint_Count=7

[LoadingHints_UTVehicleCTFGame]
Hint_0=The Hoverboard is the only vehicle that you can carry a Flag in.
Hint_1=You can use the Hoverboard's Grapple to tow behind passing friendly vehicles.
Hint_2=For a boost of speed, look for the glowing arrows that indicate a Hoverboard boost zone.
Hint_3=You can heal a friendly vehicle with the Link Gun alt-fire.
Hint_4=If you take any damage while riding the Hoverboard, you will fall to the ground and drop the Flag if you were carrying it.
Hint_5=The Paladin has a large shield, and can discharge the shield to create a very effective area of effect attack against close range targets.
Hint_Count=6

[LoadingHints_UTCTFGame]
Hint_0=Use your Translocator to teleport across the battlefield, and gain ground on enemy Flag carriers.
Hint_1=Using the Translocator to teleport while carrying the Flag will cause you to drop the Flag.
Hint_2=Toggle your Translocator key to quickly switch between the Translocator and your previous weapon.
Hint_Count=3

[LoadingHints_UTTeamGame]
Hint_0=Use the Link Gun to link with other Link Gun-carrying teammates. The head of a linked chain will receive a significant power boost to their Link Gun.
Hint_Count=1






